1.title: Spanish Seaside Adventure

episode of.title: Ocean Treks with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2016– )

1.plot: Jeff's ship arrives in Vigo, Spain where he discovers an ancient civilization that once thrived along this dramatic coastline. Then, he experiences the local seafood culture firsthand by harvesting mussels, before scrambling the rocky coastline with a spear to gather a prized delicacy.

2.title: Adventure on the Thai Seas

episode of.title: Ocean Treks with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2016– )

2.plot: Jeff's ship arrives to Phuket, Thailand where he kayaks through the spectacular Phang Nga Bay and discovers bat-filled sea caves. Next, he lends a hand to a sea turtle conservation program and teams up with a Thai chef for a tantalizing trip to the market for an exquisite Thai food experience.

3.title: Caribbean Bat Cave

episode of.title: Ocean Treks with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2016– )

3.plot: Jeff sails to the island of Curacao where he explores a historic cave and its tiny long-tongued bats. Then, he goes spearfishing for lionfish to help protect the island's precious ecosystem, before diving to discover Caribbean marine life and prized coral reefs.

4.title: Jumbos in Colombo

episode of.title: Ocean Treks with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2016– )

4.plot: Jeff's ship docks in Colombo, Sri Lanka where he visits a sanctuary to care for rescued Asian elephants. Then, he experiences the city's historic Pettah Market and its myriad of exotic flavors, before a breathtaking adventure canyoning a rainforest waterfall.

5.title: Captain Corwin

episode of.title: Ocean Treks with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2016– )

5.plot: Jeff sails to Amsterdam, Netherlands and explores the world's largest flower auction. In addition, he learns the traditional Dutch way to make Gouda cheese from a local family. His final task is navigating a cruise ship into port in a virtual training simulator.

6.title: Jewel of Japan

episode of.title: Ocean Treks with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2016– )

6.plot: Jeff cruises to Kanazawa, Japan and discovers the ancient practice of yabusame archery. He explores a mouthwatering seafood market that's stood for 300 years and takes in the scenic banks of the Sai River while learning an ancient samurai technique for fishing.

7.title: Nature Island

episode of.title: Ocean Treks with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2016– )

7.plot: Jeff's ship arrives in Dominica, the Nature Island of the Caribbean, where he discovers the wildlife of the rainforest and descends a 200-foot waterfall. On a dive, Jeff explores a vibrant coral reef and feels geothermal activity below the seafloor. He wraps his adventure by catching a bounty of fresh fish for a delicious beach cookout and carnival celebration.

8.title: A French Classic

episode of.title: Ocean Treks with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2016– )

8.plot: Jeff's ship docks in Le Havre and he explores the coast of France beginning with the ancient, towering icon of Mont St. Michel. Next, Jeff experiences escargot, a French favorite culinary tradition, and visits Utah Beach, the site of WWII's D-Day.

9.title: Tuscan Adventure

episode of.title: Ocean Treks with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2016– )

9.plot: Jeff cruises to Livorno, Italy where he explores Tuscany and saddles up with the region's famous butteri cowboys. Then, he teams up with a local chef to forage for wild porcini mushrooms and cook an Italian masterpiece in the "cucina." Jeff wraps up his adventure wandering the ancient Roman amphitheater of Volterra with its lead archaeologist.

10.title: Adventure in Oz

episode of.title: Ocean Treks with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2016– )

10.plot: Jeff's ship arrives in Sydney Harbor, where he climbs the iconic Harbor Bridge for the ultimate view of this gorgeous coastal city. Then, he discovers the amazing local wildlife and one of Australia's many endemic species, the wombat. To cap off his adventure ,Jeff gets immersed in the nature of Blue Mountains National Park by traversing a deep canyon and waterfall.

11.title: Seaside Adventures

episode of.title: Ocean Treks with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2016– )

11.plot: Jeff sets sail in search of the planet's ultimate seaside adventures. In Curacao, he explores a precious coral reef while helping to protect the ecosystem. Then, Jeff paddles between the breathtaking limestone wonders of Phuket, Thailand, and visits a towering icon in La Havre, France. Lastly, he harvests and cooks a treasured seafood on the coast of Spain.

12.title: Uncovering Lisbon

episode of.title: Ocean Treks with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2016– )

12.plot: Jeff cruises to Lisbon, Portugal, and discovers why it's become a global hot spot for dinosaur experts and curious travelers alike as he teams with a renowned local archaeologist to uncover prehistoric fossils and dinosaur bones. Next, he takes the ultimate cultural food tour through Lisbon's oldest market and dives into the Atlantic to study seahorses for scientific research.

13.title: Luck of the Irish

episode of.title: Ocean Treks with Jeff Corwin (TV Series 2016– )

13.plot: Jeff and his family arrive in the amazing port city of Dublin, Ireland where they feed seal pups at a rescue center and release one back to the wild. After collecting lobsters from the Irish Sea, the family enjoys an Irish feast overlooking the dramatic coastline below. Finally, Jeff's daughter takes the stage for a rousing Irish dancing performance.

Finally, Jeff releases a rehabilitated bat back into the wild.

Finally, Jeff gets hands on with the amazing process of restoring a 15th Century masterpiece.

Jeff ends his adventure discovering the unique wildlife that live in the country's wetlands.

He ends his adventure at a rainforest wildlife sanctuary with native baby animals.
